OL,6,FIf you drive through the centre of the
OL,7,Fcapital Lusaka, you will see dozens of
OL,8,Fsigns advertising borehole drilling as
OL,9,Fpeople look to get their own reliable
OL,10,Fsources of water.
OL,12,FBut with so much demand and so little
OL,13,Frain, the boreholes which used to sit
OL,14,Faround 50 metres are now being drilled
OL,15,Fup to 120 metres below ground.
OL,17,FThe country had a bad outbreak of
OL,18,Fcholera last year and with water
OL,19,Fsources dwindling, the government and
OL,20,Faid agencies worry there could be
OL,21,Fanother rise in the disease.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/19
